      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2) How to ensure accuracy with Inventory DB\n\nThe inventory DB is the most important DB as it is crucial to actually selling\na product. If this is down, we can't take any orders. So we protect it as much\nas possible from user facing traffic. It will only be used in the purchase journey,\nnot for browse queries.\n\nThe are two crucial tables, as outlined in the arch diagram. One to hold available\nstock, one to hold pending orders so items and prices are reserved during a payment\njourney. Transactions are super important here. When an order is created, a \npending order entry will be made. The quanity of stock will be reduce at the \nsame time. If the order isn't completed after a given time, the pending order will\nmove to 'expired' status and the inventory quantity will reset.\n\nWe can scale this through partitoning and we can partition on productId. \nProduct ID, will be noisy for popular products, but since 2000 per day max\nthis will be fine.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2) How to ensure accuracy with Inventory DB\n\nThe inventory DB is the most important DB as it is crucial to actually selling\na product. If this is down, we can't take any orders. So we protect it as much\nas possible from user facing traffic. It will only be used in the purchase journey,\nnot for browse queries.\n\nThe are two crucial tables, as outlined in the arch diagram. One to hold available\nstock, one to hold pending orders so items and prices are reserved during a payment\njourney. Transactions are super important here. When an order is created, a \npending order entry will be made. The quanity of stock will be reduce at the \nsame time. If the order isn't completed after a given time, the pending order will\nmove to 'expired' status and the inventory quantity will reset.\n\nWe can scale this through partitoning and we can partition on productId. \nProduct ID, will be noisy for popular products, but since 2000 per day max\nthis will be fine.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PIc96WQNGj50VaO0a6RFj",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 5052.1796264101085,
      "y": 376.067624853031,
      "width": 742.1195068359375,
      "height": 225,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bBt",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1527147448,
      "version": 464,
      "versionNonce": 643435976,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770992531997,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "3) For the async purchase journey. When a purchase is created we will put a\nnotification on a queue to indicate this, and kick of the order management\nprocess. \n\nWe'd have topics for... (list out the different steps)\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "3) For the async purchase journey. When a purchase is created we will put a\nnotification on a queue to indicate this, and kick of the order management\nprocess. \n\nWe'd have topics for... (list out the different steps)\n\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
